    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-03-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-03-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="87"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                <head>87. Memorandum from <persName corresp="#p_KC_1">Kaysen</persName> for the
                    Record, March 1<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d87fn1">Principals Committee
                        discussion on disarmament stages. Secret. 1 p. Kennedy Library, National
                        Security Files, Kaysen Series, Disarmament, Basic Memoranda,
                        2/62–4/62.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-03-01">March 1, 1962</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d87-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d87-1"/>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Meeting of the Committee of Principals, March 1, 1962, 2:30 P.M.</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PRESENT</head>
                    <item>Secretaries <persName corresp="#p_RD_1">Rusk</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_MRS_1">McNamara</persName>, General <persName
                            corresp="#p_LLL_1">Lemnitzer</persName>, Messrs. <persName
                            corresp="#p_FWC_1">Foster</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SGT_1"
                            >Seaborg</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MER_1">Murrow</persName>,
                            <persName corresp="#p_WJB_1">Wiesner</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_BM_1">Bundy</persName>, and others, including <persName
                            corresp="#p_HLJ_1">Haworth</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MGC_1"
                            >McGhee</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_RWW_1">Rostow</persName>,
                            <persName corresp="#p_FAS_1">Fisher</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NPH_1">Nitze</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_DA_1"
                            >Dean</persName>, Beam, <persName corresp="#p_KC_1">Kaysen</persName>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>After a great deal of discussion, <persName corresp="#p_RD_1">Rusk</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_MRS_1">McNamara</persName> indicated they thought an
                    approach to the 30% cut across the board as a first stage proposal applying to
                    the U.S. and the Soviet Union alone was the most promising approach. <persName
                        corresp="#p_FWC_1">Foster</persName> indicated that he continued to see an
                    advantage in focusing strategic vehicles only for the first stage.</p>
                <p>It was agreed that three subcommittees should look intensively with an early
                    deadline (Monday?) on three questions: the plan on the first basis; the plan on
                    the second basis; and the problems of where to have a production cutoff,
                    including the problems of how to specify the reduction.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BM_1">Bundy</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_MER_1"
                        >Murrow</persName> indicated the importance of making a strong impression
                    and being in a position to counter Russian propaganda proposals. <persName
                        corresp="#p_WJB_1">Wiesner</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_KC_1"
                        >Kaysen</persName> emphasized the importance of inspection procedures and of
                    having some specific view on inspection for the conference. <persName
                        corresp="#p_NPH_1">Nitze</persName> expressed concern as to whether a zonal
                    inspection system was one which Defense could agree on. It was agreed that the
                    report of the inspection subcommittee now in process would be expected on
                    Monday. March 5</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_KC_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KC_1">Carl Kaysen</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
